{
  "_provenance": {
    "what": "Canonical human molecular target(s) for each drug in the docking panel, used to look up the two orthogonal evidence axes (pathway grounding + DepMap dependency) against data/gene_kb.json.",
    "source": "Curated from DrugBank / ChEMBL / package-insert mechanism of action. Targets are the drug's ESTABLISHED targets, not the docked protein: the point of the axes is to ask whether a drug's real biology has any business at the driver's pathway. Genes must exist in data/gene_kb.json ('BACTERIAL' / 'VIRAL' / 'NONE' are sentinels for non-human or undefined targets). Drugs not listed default to target 'NONE'.",
    "note": "Multi-target kinase drugs list their principal kinase targets. imatinib is deliberately mapped to its real targets (ABL1/KIT/PDGFR), NOT to EGFR: its EGFR relevance here is a STRUCTURAL cross-binding hypothesis from docking, which is exactly why its dependency axis reads 'weak' while its docking Delta is a gain."
  },
